# Catalog Service Rules

## Architecture & layering

- Follow the four-project layout: `Catalog.API` (HTTP/DI) → `Catalog.Application` (handlers) → `Catalog.Core` (entities/interfaces) → `Catalog.Infrastructure` (MongoDB, S3).
- Add new endpoints as Mediator commands/queries + handlers in `Catalog.Application`; keep controllers thin — delegate via `_mediator.Send()`.
- Use `ProductMapper.Instance` (Mapperly) for entity/DTO mapping; do not register mappers in DI.
- `ProductRepository` is the single implementation for `IProductRepository`, `IBrandRepository`, and `ITypesRepository` — extend it, do not create parallel repository classes.

## Data & persistence

- MongoDB collections are `Products`, `Brands`, `Types` — configured via `DatabaseSettings` in `appsettings.json`.
- Seed data lives in `Catalog.Infrastructure/Data/SeedData/`; product seed file switches on `USE_LOCALSTACK` env var.
- Pagination/filtering goes through `CatalogSpecParams` → `ProductRepository.GetProducts` — respect `MaxPageSize` (70).
- Do not add EF Core or alternate ORMs; persistence is MongoDB driver only.

## Messaging & events

- Publish integration events via MassTransit `IPublishEndpoint` — event type is `ProductActivityEvent` from `Infrastructure/EventBus.Messages`.
- Today only `CreateProduct` and `UpdateProduct` publish events; `Actor` is hardcoded `"system"`.
- MassTransit host is `EventBusSettings:HostAddress` (RabbitMQ).

## Images & S3

- Image uploads flow through `UploadProductImageCommand` → `S3ImageStorageService`.
- S3 client switches between LocalStack (`USE_LOCALSTACK=true` + `AWS_ENDPOINT_URL`) and real AWS based on `Program.cs` branching.
- Validate against `ImageSettings` (5 MB max, `.png/.jpg/.jpeg/.webp`).

## Security & config

- No authentication middleware is configured — do not assume JWT or role claims exist.
- CORS is fully permissive (`AllowAnyOrigin`).
- `ElasticConfiguration` and Mongo health-check packages are referenced but not wired in `Program.cs`.

## Common pitfalls

- Seed methods use un-awaited `InsertOneAsync` — race conditions possible on cold start.
- `GetProductById` does not return 404 for missing products.
- Admin migration (`MigrateImagesToS3`) requires `/app/images/products` volume mount from compose.
- Gateway routes Catalog at port 8000 via Ocelot (`/Catalog/...` → `/api/v1/Catalog/...`).

